declarations.comments:
A pairing between functors `f` and `g`.

This asserts that any sums in `f` can annihilate any products in `g`, and vice
versa.

This library provides some useful pairings, and ways of lifting pairings over
various constructions on `Functor`s.
declarations.title: Pairing

declarations.comments: The identity functor pairs with itself
declarations.title: identity

declarations.comments: Functor products pair with functor coproducts
declarations.title: productCoproduct

declarations.comments: `w` pairs with `Co w` whenever `w` is a `Functor`.
declarations.title: pairCo
